description:
## Task
When workspace is a directory containing multiple repos (like ~/projects), show the multi-repo dashboard view instead of single WorkingTree.

## Requirements
- Detect if workspace contains multiple git repos vs is itself a repo
- If multiple repos: show RepoCard list (current SourceControl behavior)
- If single repo: show WorkingTree
- Preserve bulk operations (fetch/pull/push all) for multi-repo view
- Search/filter repos in multi-repo view

## Detection Logic
```ts
// Check if workspace itself is a git repo
const isRepo = await checkIsGitRepo(workspacePath);
if (isRepo) {
  return <WorkingTree repoPath={workspacePath} />;
} else {
  return <MultiRepoView projectsDir={workspacePath} />;
}
```

## Note
This makes the view workspace-aware - selecting ~/projects shows dashboard, selecting ~/projects/foo shows just foo's status.

Add 'Edit' context menu action that spawns a new terminal with $EDITOR on the file.

Use TabzChrome's /api/spawn endpoint:
POST /api/spawn { command: "$EDITOR /path/to/file", workingDir: "..." }

