## prepared.prompt

Replace the split view dropdown with drag-and-drop tab functionality for a more intuitive UX.

**Context:** Currently the right split pane has a dropdown to select from recent files. Dragging tabs to the right pane (like VS Code) would be more intuitive.

**Files to modify:**
- `src/components/TabBar.tsx` - Add drag source functionality to tabs
- `src/components/SplitView.tsx` - Add drop target for right pane
- `src/pages/Files.tsx` - Handle drop events, remove dropdown logic

**Implementation:**

1. **TabBar.tsx - Make tabs draggable:**
   ```tsx
   <div
     draggable
     onDragStart={(e) => {
       e.dataTransfer.setData("text/plain", tab.path);
       e.dataTransfer.effectAllowed = "move";
     }}
     // ... existing tab content
   >
   ```

2. **SplitView.tsx - Add drop zone to right pane:**
   ```tsx
   const [isDragOver, setIsDragOver] = useState(false);

   // Right pane wrapper
   <div
     onDragOver={(e) => {
       e.preventDefault();
       setIsDragOver(true);
     }}
     onDragLeave={() => setIsDragOver(false)}
     onDrop={(e) => {
       e.preventDefault();
       const path = e.dataTransfer.getData("text/plain");
       onDropToRight?.(path);
       setIsDragOver(false);
     }}
     style={{
       outline: isDragOver ? "2px dashed var(--accent)" : "none"
     }}
   >
   ```

3. **Visual feedback:**
   - Dashed outline on right pane when dragging over
   - Ghost image of tab while dragging
   - "Drop here" placeholder text when pane is empty and dragging

4. **Files.tsx changes:**
   - Add `handleDropToRight(path)` handler
   - Remove dropdown from right pane header
   - Show file name in header instead (with close button)

5. **Edge cases:**
   - Dragging to right when not in split mode: auto-enable split
   - Dragging same file that's already in right: no-op
   - Close button in right pane header to clear right file

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] Tabs are draggable
- [ ] Dragging over right pane shows drop indicator
- [ ] Dropping tab opens file in right pane
- [ ] Visual feedback during drag
- [ ] Remove dropdown from right pane
- [ ] Right pane header shows current file name
- [ ] Close button to clear right pane

When complete, commit and run `bd close markdown-themes-diy`.

## prepared.prompt

## Context
JSONL (JSON Lines) files store one JSON object per line. Useful for viewing .beads/issues.jsonl and Claude Code logs.

## Task
Create a JSONL file viewer component.

## Key Files
- src/components/viewers/JsonlViewer.tsx - NEW file to create
- src/components/viewers/JsonViewer.tsx - reference for JSON tree rendering
- src/components/ViewerContainer.tsx - add routing for .jsonl extension

## Implementation
1. Create JsonlViewer.tsx:
```tsx
export function JsonlViewer({ content, fontSize = 100 }: { content: string; fontSize?: number }) {
  const lines = useMemo(() => {
    return content.split('\n')
      .filter(line => line.trim())
      .map((line, idx) => {
        try {
          return { id: idx, data: JSON.parse(line), error: null };
        } catch (e) {
          return { id: idx, data: null, error: e.message };
        }
      });
  }, [content]);

  // Render each line as collapsible JSON tree
  // Reuse JsonNode from JsonViewer or inline similar logic
}
```

2. Update ViewerContainer.tsx:
- Add: `const jsonlExtensions = new Set(['jsonl', 'ndjson']);`
- Add check in getViewerType()
- Add case in switch to render JsonlViewer

3. Create JsonlViewer.test.ts with basic tests

## When Done
Run `npm run test:run` then: bd close markdown-themes-dtn --reason "Added JSONL viewer with line-by-line JSON display"
